1.00	Heart_of_stone_(medicine)	Calciphylaxis	Calciphylaxis is a syndrome of vascular calcification, thrombosis and skin necrosis. It is seen almost exclusively in patients with Stage 5 chronic kidney disease. It results in chronic non-healing wounds and is usually fatal. Calciphylaxis is a rare but serious disease.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5c/Calciphylaxis.png/300px-Calciphylaxis.png
